Look. You'll stay in that bed.

121
00:11:40,500 --> 00:11:44,500
We have a newcomer in our ward.

122
00:11:46,800 --> 00:11:48,700
Oh, it's you?

123
00:11:48,700 --> 00:11:52,400
We have met before. Do you remember me?

124
00:11:52,400 --> 00:11:55,500
Yes. Uncle Guo.

125
00:11:55,500 --> 00:11:57,600
This is your boyfriend?

126
00:11:57,600 --> 00:12:01,000
What a coincidence.

127
00:12:01,000 --> 00:12:02,700
Do you know each other?

128
00:12:02,700 --> 00:12:04,200
Yes.

129
00:12:04,200 --> 00:12:09,400
Xiao Que has been working here as a caregiver for a while.

130
00:12:09,400 --> 00:12:12,000
She keeps mentioning her boyfriend.

131
00:12:14,100 --> 00:12:16,300
You have been working here as a caretaker?

132
00:12:16,300 --> 00:12:20,400
Not really. I came here to be a volunteer and learn some nursing knowledge.

133
00:12:20,400 --> 00:12:23,500
It's not that easy to be a caretaker.

134
00:12:24,200 --> 00:12:28,000
Then you chat with Uncle Guo. I'll go do the paperwork.

135
00:12:28,000 --> 00:12:30,800
- I'm off. Bye. 
 - Go ahead.

136
00:12:34,300 --> 00:12:37,800
Your girlfriend is really nice.

137
00:12:37,800 --> 00:12:44,700
She has been volunteering here for quite some time to study nursing.

138
00:12:44,700 --> 00:12:46,900
That's rare.

139
00:12:47,800 --> 00:12:50,400
I didn't even know about that.

140
00:12:51,200 --> 00:12:55,000
I've been a burden to her.

141
00:12:56,200 --> 00:12:57,900
You are a family.

142
00:12:57,900 --> 00:13:01,900
It's inevitable we would be a burden to each other.

143
00:13:01,900 --> 00:13:04,400
You'll feel at ease here.

144
00:13:04,400 --> 00:13:07,300
We have a little patient here in our ward.

145
00:13:07,300 --> 00:13:09,200
It's a little boy.

146
00:13:09,200 --> 00:13:11,200
He's staying in that bed.

147
00:13:11,200 --> 00:13:12,800
We're back.

148
00:13:12,800 --> 00:13:15,400
- Dong Dong. 
 - Uncle Guo.

149
00:13:15,400 --> 00:13:18,000
We have a newcomer in our ward.

150
00:13:18,600 --> 00:13:20,100
What's your name?

151
00:13:20,100 --> 00:13:21,300
Lin Tuo.

152
00:13:21,300 --> 00:13:24,200
Xiao Lin, this is Dong Dong and Dong Dong's mom.

153
00:13:24,200 --> 00:13:26,500
Just call her Sister Yan'er.

154
00:13:26,500 --> 00:13:29,200
- Hello, Sister Yan'er. 
 - Hello. This is my son.

155
00:13:29,200 --> 00:13:31,600
- Dong Dong, say hello. 
 - Hello, Brother.

156
00:13:31,600 --> 00:13:33,100
Hello, Dong Dong.

157
00:13:33,100 --> 00:13:35,300
Let's go have some water.

158
00:13:35,300 --> 00:13:39,700
Look. It's fate for us to live in the same ward.

159
00:13:39,700 --> 00:13:43,700
It's lively now, right?

160
00:13:43,700 --> 00:13:49,000
I'll show you around and make some introduction.

161
00:13:51,300 --> 00:13:55,600
Xiao Lin, join our group, Light of Hope.

162
00:13:55,600 --> 00:13:57,800
They're all patients here.

163
00:13:57,800 --> 00:14:02,200
Every day, we share nursing and treatment info, 
    

164
00:14:02,200 --> 00:14:06,900
and things to take note. It's so useful.

165
00:14:06,900 --> 00:14:09,900
Xiao Que. Help Xiao Lin join our group later.

166
00:14:09,900 --> 00:14:12,400
Okay, I'll do it.

167
00:14:13,900 --> 00:14:16,900
Dong Dong is really well-behaved today.

168
00:14:16,900 --> 00:14:18,400
What are you eating?

169
00:14:18,400 --> 00:14:22,700
- Noodles. 
 - Noodles. They look very delicious.

170
00:14:22,700 --> 00:14:27,100
Eat well. Eating properly can make you grow up fast.

171
00:14:27,100 --> 00:14:31,200
- Have you eaten? 
 - Yes. I just ate.

172
00:14:31,900 --> 00:14:36,000
Old Xiao from the first floor took a fall. He was making a fuss.

173
00:14:36,000 --> 00:14:39,100
I just went to talk to him.

174
00:14:39,100 --> 00:14:43,300
He vented his anger to his wife, making her so mad.

175
00:14:43,300 --> 00:14:49,700
Say, having a wife to take care of him is such a great blessing.

176
00:14:49,700 --> 00:14:54,300
Yet, he's still not satisfied. Later I'll go and talk to him again.

177
00:14:55,648 --> 00:14:57,300
Have you two eaten?

178
00:14:57,300 --> 00:14:58,900
Not yet.

179
00:14:58,900 --> 00:15:01,900
Hurry and go get some. There is food in the canteen.

180
00:15:01,900 --> 00:15:03,500
Today's dishes are good.

181
00:15:03,500 --> 00:15:05,600
All right, I'll go later.

182
00:15:05,600 --> 00:15:07,700
Uncle Guo.

183
00:15:07,700 --> 00:15:10,000
- Uncle Guo, I need you! 
 - Who is it?

184
00:15:10,000 --> 00:15:11,500
Coming.

185
00:15:11,500 --> 00:15:14,500
Can you help me with this ventilator?

186
00:15:20,000 --> 00:15:24,200
Uncle Guo speaks like a host in a training session.

187
00:15:24,200 --> 00:15:25,700
Thanks to him.

188
00:15:25,700 --> 00:15:29,600
When people here can no longer hold on, it's Uncle Guo who soothes them.

189
00:15:29,600 --> 00:15:32,200
Uncle Guo's illness doesn't seem to be very serious.

190
00:15:32,200 --> 00:15:34,600
With such good spirits.

191
00:15:34,600 --> 00:15:37,500
He's been like this for three years. His right hand can still move.

192
00:15:37,500 --> 00:15:40,200
The doctor said he has a strong will.

193
00:15:40,200 --> 00:15:42,600
Sometimes, I think he's healthy.

194
00:15:42,600 --> 00:15:44,600
He's so energetic.

195
00:15:46,500 --> 00:15:50,600
- Mom, I don't want to eat anymore. 
 - Just a few more bites.

196
00:15:50,600 --> 00:15:52,700
Finish it and you'll grow taller.

197
00:15:52,700 --> 00:15:55,300
Baby, be good.

198
00:15:56,100 --> 00:15:59,700
How can you grow taller or get better if you don't eat?

199
00:15:59,700 --> 00:16:02,600
Dong Dong, look. What is this?

200
00:16:02,600 --> 00:16:04,500
A lollipop.

201
00:16:04,500 --> 00:16:08,600
You have to finish eating. And then we can have the lollipop, okay?

202
00:16:08,600 --> 00:16:10,300
Eat up.

203
00:16:10,300 --> 00:16:12,900
Come on, take a big bite.

204
00:16:13,500 --> 00:16:15,700
Good.

205
00:16:15,700 --> 00:16:17,700
Thanks, Xiao Que.

206
00:16:18,500 --> 00:16:20,400
Another bite.

207
00:16:27,700 --> 00:16:29,800
I've put the water by your bedside.

208
00:16:29,800 --> 00:16:32,400
If you need anything, just tell the caregiver.

209
00:16:32,400 --> 00:16:34,900
She makes rounds every night.

210
00:16:36,700 --> 00:16:39,400
Just call me if you need anything.

211
00:16:40,000 --> 00:16:41,100
Xiao Que.

212
00:16:41,100 --> 00:16:46,700
Just go. I'll take good care of Xiao Lin for you.

213
00:16:46,700 --> 00:16:48,400
Thank you, Uncle Guo.

214
00:16:48,400 --> 00:16:50,400
Don't mention it.

215
00:16:51,200 --> 00:16:53,900
I'm leaving then. I'll come see you tomorrow.

216
00:16:53,900 --> 00:16:57,000
You go with your work. Come after you finish.

217
00:16:58,500 --> 00:17:00,400
- Good night. 
 - Good night.

218
00:17:00,400 --> 00:17:01,700
I'm leaving.

219
00:17:01,700 --> 00:17:03,100
Goodbye, Uncle Guo.

220
00:17:03,100 --> 00:17:05,600
- Goodbye, be careful on the road. 
 - Okay.

221
00:17:05,600 --> 00:17:07,200
Bye-bye.

222
00:17:31,600 --> 00:17:32,900
Sister Yan'er.

223
00:17:32,900 --> 00:17:34,600
- Xiao Que. 
 - You are still working?

224
00:17:34,600 --> 00:17:38,500
Right. Dong Dong just fell asleep, so I can get the work done. Leaving?

225
00:17:38,500 --> 00:17:42,900
Xiao Tuo is moving in today. Please take care of him if you can.

226
00:17:42,900 --> 00:17:47,100
- Sure thing. Don't worry. Be careful. 
 - All right, I'm off.

227
00:17:47,100 --> 00:17:49,700
- Sorry I would step on it. 
 - It's okay. Careful. It's slippery.

228
00:17:49,700 --> 00:17:52,500
- Goodbye, Sister Yan'er. 
 - Bye.

229
00:19:09,500 --> 00:19:11,700
- Lin Tuo. 
 - Keep your voice down.

230
00:19:11,700 --> 00:19:14,000
- We are here.
- Lin Tuo.

