00:20:32,860 --> 00:20:35,460
   

256
00:20:40,900 --> 00:20:43,000
Time to eat.

257
00:20:45,000 --> 00:20:46,600
I'm not hungry.

258
00:20:46,600 --> 00:20:49,000
You should eat some.

259
00:20:50,000 --> 00:20:51,800
Don't want to eat.

260
00:20:54,100 --> 00:20:57,000
Do you find it boring here?

261
00:20:57,800 --> 00:20:59,300
No.

262
00:21:01,700 --> 00:21:03,300
Xiao Lin.

263
00:21:03,300 --> 00:21:05,900
- Uncle Guo. 
 - Want to watch the game?

264
00:21:05,900 --> 00:21:07,400
Yes.

265
00:21:07,400 --> 00:21:09,500
- Come on, Uncle Guo. 
 - Okay.

266
00:21:09,500 --> 00:21:12,000
What are you watching?

267
00:21:12,000 --> 00:21:14,400
World Cup qualifiers.

268
00:21:14,400 --> 00:21:17,000
- China vs. Philippines, right? 
 - Yes.

269
00:21:17,000 --> 00:21:18,800
- Can you see it? 
 - Yes.

270
00:21:18,800 --> 00:21:21,000
I'll go get some water for you.

271
00:21:21,000 --> 00:21:23,000
Header.

272
00:21:23,000 --> 00:21:24,900
What's the score?

273
00:21:25,500 --> 00:21:27,400
One to zero.

274
00:21:29,200 --> 00:21:32,100
- Run! 
 - Pass the ball! Pass...

275
00:21:32,100 --> 00:21:34,300
If I could...

276
00:21:36,100 --> 00:21:37,200
Good.

277
00:21:37,200 --> 00:21:40,100
- Got penalized again. 
 - Oh my.

278
00:22:11,900 --> 00:22:14,600
A'Bao, what time is it?

279
00:22:14,600 --> 00:22:18,500
- It's almost 11. 
 - 11 o'clock. I have to go deliver food.

280
00:22:18,500 --> 00:22:20,800
Isn't there a caregiver over there?

281
00:22:20,800 --> 00:22:25,900
I can't let Xiao Tuo think he's left alone just because he's in the nursing home. Right?

282
00:22:25,900 --> 00:22:27,800
- Yes. 
 - I'm leaving.

283
00:22:27,800 --> 00:22:30,500
- Take care. 
 - You go ahead.

284
00:22:35,700 --> 00:22:38,300
Hello, Auntie.

285
00:23:34,500 --> 00:23:36,200
Dad.

286
00:23:37,900 --> 00:23:39,400
Dad.

287
00:23:47,300 --> 00:23:49,200
Uncle.

288
00:23:49,200 --> 00:23:51,000
Xiao Tuo.

289
00:23:53,700 --> 00:23:55,900
Come say your goodbyes.

290
00:23:57,400 --> 00:23:59,500
What happened?

291
00:24:01,000 --> 00:24:04,900
He suddenly fainted while playing gateball this morning.

292
00:24:04,900 --> 00:24:08,600
He has a heart condition that he kept from you.

293
00:24:08,600 --> 00:24:13,500
During the resuscitation, he kept calling your name.

294
00:24:43,800 --> 00:24:45,600
Grandpa.

295
00:24:47,200 --> 00:24:50,800
Xiao Tuo and I are here to see you.

296
00:24:52,400 --> 00:24:54,200
Grandpa.

297
00:25:19,700 --> 00:25:21,500
Grandpa.

298
00:25:25,800 --> 00:25:27,900
It's me, Xiao Tuo.

299
00:25:31,900 --> 00:25:33,600
Grandpa.

300
00:26:06,300 --> 00:26:11,400
 Grandpa. I thought I would be the first to leave.  
    

301
00:26:11,400 --> 00:26:15,700
 I've thought about it. If I were the one to leave first, 

302
00:26:15,700 --> 00:26:18,400
 how would I say goodbye to you? 

303
00:26:20,500 --> 00:26:26,400
 From the first day I learned of my illness, I've rehearsed it countless times in my mind. 

304
00:26:26,400 --> 00:26:31,700
 But no matter how many times I rehearsed, I still can't be prepared. 

305
00:26:34,700 --> 00:26:37,600
 I thought this life would be long, 

306
00:26:38,400 --> 00:26:42,200
 but never expected to face death so soon. 

307
00:26:43,700 --> 00:26:49,000
 Grandpa. It won't be long. Just wait for me. 

308
00:26:49,700 --> 00:26:53,600
 Let's meet in heaven. 

309
00:27:25,100 --> 00:27:28,900
Auntie. Hasn't he eaten?

310
00:27:28,900 --> 00:27:31,000
He's been sleeping.

311
00:27:40,600 --> 00:27:42,400
Xiao Tuo.

312
00:27:44,800 --> 00:27:46,600
Xiao Tuo.

313
00:27:49,000 --> 00:27:52,900
Auntie, just let him sleep for a while.

314
00:27:56,000 --> 00:27:58,000
I'll stay here.

315
00:27:58,000 --> 00:28:01,800
His dad has gone to the hospital. You go back and rest for a bit.

316
00:28:01,800 --> 00:28:05,200
I'll go to the hospital as well. Then please stay here and keep Xiao Tuo company.

317
00:28:05,200 --> 00:28:08,300
- Okay. Go on. 
 - I'm leaving.

318
00:28:37,300 --> 00:28:41,930
Grandpa passed away so suddenly. Xiao Tuo must be unable to take it.

319
00:28:41,930 --> 00:28:43,900
   

320
00:28:43,900 --> 00:28:46,800
This is really adding insult to injury.

321
00:28:46,800 --> 00:28:49,900
His condition will surely be affected.

322
00:28:49,900 --> 00:28:52,500
Let's give him some time.

323
00:28:52,500 --> 00:28:56,800
He's been holding it together since then.

324
00:28:56,800 --> 00:29:00,000
I'm worried he wouldn't make it this time.

325
00:29:02,200 --> 00:29:09,000
Once the mind collapses, the body can't take it anymore.

326
00:29:11,300 --> 00:29:15,500
Don't worry. I am right there with him.

327
00:29:17,000 --> 00:29:18,300
Thank you.

328
00:29:18,300 --> 00:29:20,000
Not at all.

329
00:29:23,000 --> 00:29:28,400
Because of grandpa's death, Xiao Tuo's mom has been crying these few days.

330
00:29:28,400 --> 00:29:33,300
But she can't show her sadness in front of Xiao Tuo.

331
00:29:35,000 --> 00:29:37,600
But she's quite...

332
00:29:38,600 --> 00:29:42,100
Uncle, keep her good company.

333
00:29:42,100 --> 00:29:45,700
None of us can collapse at this point.

334
00:29:45,700 --> 00:29:49,500
Right. We can't break.

335
00:29:49,500 --> 00:29:51,800
None of us can.

336
00:29:52,700 --> 00:29:55,700
Are you kidding? I can't be hospitalized.

337
00:29:55,700 --> 00:29:58,400
Is this diagnosis correct? I don't accept it.

338
00:29:58,400 --> 00:30:01,200
Enough. I'm going to find the director.

339
00:30:02,900 --> 00:30:05,300
I'm sorry, Director Zhou. We'll meet next time.

340
00:30:05,300 --> 00:30:08,000
Mr. Gao. Wait for me.

341
00:30:08,700 --> 00:30:10,620
Let's go inside.

342
00:30:10,620 --> 00:30:16,100
   

343
00:30:16,100 --> 00:30:21,100
Many patients have this psychological reaction after hearing the diagnosis.

344
00:30:21,100 --> 00:30:23,700
He'd deny it, hoping it's wrong.

345
00:30:23,700 --> 00:30:27,200
Lin Tuo was the same when the diagnosis first came out.

346
00:30:27,200 --> 00:30:30,000
This is all normal.

347
00:30:30,000 --> 00:30:33,000
This happens all the time in hospitals.

348
00:30:33,000 --> 00:30:35,600
Let alone ordinary patients, even I...

349
00:30:35,600 --> 00:30:41,000
After Xiao Tuo fell ill, I wish every day it was a misdiagnosis.

350
00:30:41,800 --> 00:30:43,000
I understand.

351
00:30:43,000 --> 00:30:45,700
Director Zhou. Ever since Xiao Tuo got sick,

352
00:30:45,700 --> 00:30:49,700
my classmates and teachers from medical school have been running around for me,

353
00:30:49,700 --> 00:30:51,900
looking for experts and gathering information.

354
00:30:51,900 --> 00:30:55,800
And they also put me in touch with a few neurology experts.

355
00:30:55,800 --> 00:31:00,300
They recommended some meds and some complementary treatments.

356
00:31:00,300 --> 00:31:02,500
Please check if we can use them.

357
00:31:03,200 --> 00:31:08,900
Some of them do make sense, but more of them are theoretical.

358
00:31:08,900 --> 00:31:16,800
We need a further study based on the patient's specific situation, alright?

359
00:31:16,800 --> 00:31:20,400
How's Lin Tuo doing? Has he entered the nursing home?

360
00:31:20,400 --> 00:31:21,600
Yes.

361
00:31:21,600 --> 00:31:26,400
But he might not be used to living there just yet, so he's not in a good mood.

362
00:31:26,400 --> 00:31:29,400
Moreover, his grandpa has suddenly passed away.

363
00:31:29,400 --> 00:31:32,900
He couldn't take it right away, so he's not doing good recently.

364
00:31:32,900 --> 00:31:37,700
He wasn't particularly optimistic the last time he did the check-up.

365
00:31:37,700 --> 00:31:43,200
So you might need to prepare for what's next.

366
00:31:44,300 --> 00:31:46,700
What do you mean?

367
00:31:46,700 --> 00:31:48,600
I didn't mean what you think.

368
00:31:48,600 --> 00:31:53,100
The disease goes to the next level after a certain time.

369
00:31:53,100 --> 00:31:57,900
In the meantime, the patient's mood will fluctuate.

370
00:31:57,900 --> 00:32:02,000
So you need to try to get him used to this phase,

371
00:32:02,000 --> 00:32:04,700
and appropriately divert his attention.

372
00:32:04,700 --> 00:32:08,200
Especially to give him an outlet to vent his depression out.

373
00:32:08,200 --> 00:32:10,700
Don't keep holding it together. Do you understand?

374
00:32:10,700 --> 00:32:12,300
Yes.

375
00:32:23,100 --> 00:32:24,900
You must be hungry.

376
00:32:26,600 --> 00:32:29,300
Tell my mom to go back.

377
00:32:29,300 --> 00:32:33,300
At least eat something. Otherwise, she won't go back.

378
00:32:34,000 --> 00:32:37,800
Guangpu, Xindi and Senior are waiting outside.

379
00:32:37,800 --> 00:32:40,400
They are quite worried about you.

380
00:32:41,700 --> 00:32:44,400
Tell them to go back.

381
00:32:45,200 --> 00:32:47,500
I want to be alone.

382
00:32:51,000 --> 00:32:52,600
Okay.

383
00:33:14,828 --> 00:33:16,188
Xiao Que.

384
00:33:16,188 --> 00:33:18,628
- How is he? 
 - How is he?

385
00:33:18,628 --> 00:33:22,868
He doesn't want to talk or eat. He is not in a good mood.

386
00:33:22,868 --> 00:33:25,412
All right, I'll go and check on him.

387
00:33:25,412 --> 00:33:28,678
Hey. You know him.

388
00:33:28,678 --> 00:33:33,328
His body is okay right now. Just let him take his time.

389
00:33:33,328 --> 00:33:34,798
You guys go back.

390
00:33:34,798 --> 00:33:37,508
Can he keep going without eating?

391
00:33:37,508 --> 00:33:40,128
But I can't force him to eat.

392
00:33:40,128 --> 00:33:44,698
His grandpa has suddenly passed away. No one can take it.

393
00:33:46,108 --> 00:33:48,468
It happened so suddenly.

394
00:33:48,468 --> 00:33:50,388
I'll go talk to him.

395
00:33:50,388 --> 00:33:53,008
Stop. What can you say?

396
00:33:53,008 --> 00:33:54,938
His mood is definitely not good now.

397
00:33:54,938 --> 00:33:57,038
Let's come back tomorrow.

398
00:33:57,608 --> 00:34:02,168
Just leave him alone. He can't listen to anything now.

399
00:34:05,628 --> 00:34:08,088
Don't be too upset.

400
00:34:08,788 --> 00:34:10,482
Call me if you need me.

401
00:34:10,482 --> 00:34:13,352
Okay. It's fine.

402
00:34:13,352 --> 00:34:15,068
- Go on. 
 - Then we'll leave.

403
00:34:15,068 --> 00:34:16,948
Just go.

404
00:34:16,948 --> 00:34:18,748
Bye.

405
00:34:49,548 --> 00:34:51,648
Say...

406
00:34:52,308 --> 00:34:55,187
Would Lin Tuo get over it this time?

407
00:34:57,068 --> 00:34:58,968
What do you mean?

408
00:35:00,188 --> 00:35:04,768
I'm afraid he can't get over it and does silly things.

409
00:35:09,268 --> 00:35:13,448
Let's be realistic. Given Lin Tuo's current situation,

410
00:35:13,448 --> 00:35:18,928
if he wants to do something silly like that, he couldn't do it either.

411
00:35:20,168 --> 00:35:22,268
Indeed.

412
00:35:22,268 --> 00:35:26,248
He can't move, so he can't do anything he wants to, right?

413
00:35:26,248 --> 00:35:28,668
Definitely.

414
00:35:28,668 --> 00:35:31,896
But now he doesn't eat. Is he trying to starve himself?

415
00:35:31,896 --> 00:35:35,628
Wait. Can't you think of anything good? Don't talk nonsense.

416
00:35:35,628 --> 00:35:38,688
You're the one who said Lin Tuo couldn't get over it. You started it.

417
00:35:38,688 --> 00:35:40,440
Now you're blaming me?

418
00:35:40,440 --> 00:35:42,480
All right, sorry.

419
00:35:43,148 --> 00:35:45,148
I am scared.

420
00:35:45,788 --> 00:35:48,628
Maybe tell Xiao Que about it?

421
00:35:48,628 --> 00:35:50,428
Please don't.

422
00:35:50,428 --> 00:35:54,328
Don't scare Xiao Que. Can't Xiao Que think of anything you can come up with?

423
00:35:54,328 --> 00:35:56,608
She's now staying at the nursing home.

424
00:35:56,608 --> 00:35:59,008
In case something really happens...

425
00:36:00,748 --> 00:36:03,428
The nursing home could respond immediately.

426
00:36:03,428 --> 00:36:05,028
Indeed.

427
00:36:05,708 --> 00:36:07,948
Luckily, he's at the nursing home.

428
00:36:07,948 --> 00:36:11,568
Don't put our phones on mute. Be ready to respond to any situation.

429
00:36:11,568 --> 00:36:13,708
Don't sleep too soundly, hear me?

430
00:36:13,708 --> 00:36:16,068
Just make sure you don't sleep too soundly.

431
00:36:16,068 --> 00:36:17,828
Like a pig.

432
00:36:17,828 --> 00:36:22,188
How old are you? How come you snore? I'd be surprised if you get a wife.

433
00:36:22,188 --> 00:36:25,732
I-It runs in my family.

434
00:36:25,732 --> 00:36:31,968
My dad snores too. Then I'll have to marry someone who can get used to my snoring.

435
00:36:38,388 --> 00:36:41,828
Did you just look at me? D-Don't you dare!

436
00:36:41,828 --> 00:36:45,308
How dare you! I'm telling you, I can't get used to your snoring.

437
00:36:45,308 --> 00:36:47,688
Keep your eyes on the road.

438
00:37:00,708 --> 00:37:03,308
Come on, Xiao Tuo.

439
00:37:03,308 --> 00:37:05,248
Have some water.

440
00:37:13,408 --> 00:37:16,148
Your dad is going to Beijing soon.

441
00:37:16,148 --> 00:37:21,388
I'm leaving. My classmate in Beijing works for an authoritative neurology department,

442
00:37:21,388 --> 00:37:25,431
and he has made the contact. I need to pay a visit.

443
00:37:25,431 --> 00:37:28,488
Besides, I've already talked to the director.

444
00:37:28,488 --> 00:37:36,288
There are several new drugs and new treatment methods that need further study.

445
00:37:36,288 --> 00:37:38,685
Don't you need to work?

446
00:37:40,148 --> 00:37:43,248
I've taken leave. So has your mom.

447
00:37:43,248 --> 00:37:45,548
She can spend some time with you.

448
00:37:45,548 --> 00:37:47,448
I am staying here.

449
00:37:48,128 --> 00:37:50,108
You two should go back to work.

450
00:37:50,108 --> 00:37:51,868
I'm fine.

451
00:37:54,468 --> 00:37:58,504
Okay. I'll go back tomorrow.

452
00:37:59,108 --> 00:38:00,808
Xiao Tuo.

453
00:38:00,808 --> 00:38:03,048
Cheer up.

454
00:38:04,058 --> 00:38:06,288
For the sake of us,

455
00:38:06,288 --> 00:38:10,048
your grandpa, and Xiao Que,

456
00:38:10,708 --> 00:38:14,128
don't give up and eat well.

457
00:38:14,788 --> 00:38:16,588
Wait for me.

458
00:38:17,288 --> 00:38:19,368
I'm off.

459
00:38:19,368 --> 00:38:20,968
Dad.

460
00:38:24,215 --> 00:38:26,695
This disease of mine can't be cured.

461
00:38:30,868 --> 00:38:34,328
I know better than you what to do.

462
00:38:35,328 --> 00:38:36,928
Bye.

463
00:39:23,428 --> 00:39:24,908
The soup is here.

464
00:39:24,908 --> 00:39:27,688
Hurry, serve it up.

465
00:39:27,688 --> 00:39:31,548
- Look how well this soup has been stewed. 
 - It smells good.

466
00:39:33,308 --> 00:39:38,248
Xiao Que, don't overthink it. It's normal to not have an appetite.

467
00:39:38,248 --> 00:39:42,448
With such a thing happened, no one could have an appetite. Right?

468
00:39:42,448 --> 00:39:45,708
When your mom fell ill, she didn't want to eat either.

469
00:39:45,708 --> 00:39:49,418
What did I do? I made her soup. Soup is really good.

470
00:39:49,418 --> 00:39:51,708
It's flavorful and nutritious.

471
00:39:51,708 --> 00:39:55,108
B-But your mom didn't want to eat the soup either, so I forced her.

472
00:39:55,108 --> 00:39:56,928
Why? Your mom needed to drink more.

473
00:39:56,928 --> 00:39:59,100
I even tried to make all kinds of soups.

474
00:39:59,100 --> 00:40:01,637
Vegetables, fruits, milk, and yogurt...

475
00:40:01,637 --> 00:40:06,261
Anything that could be juiced, I juiced it all up for her. It's nice.

476
00:40:06,261 --> 00:40:10,208
Dad, you had a hard time taking care of my mom, right?

477
00:40:11,368 --> 00:40:15,108
Well, I didn't mind it.

478
00:40:15,108 --> 00:40:17,848
But I felt so sorry for her.

479
00:40:17,848 --> 00:40:21,568
Xiao Tuo is now particularly rejecting everyone's care.

480
00:40:23,848 --> 00:40:26,208
Today, he even drove his mom away.

481
00:40:26,208 --> 00:40:29,808
I told him I'd bring him your cooking.

482
00:40:29,808 --> 00:40:33,308
He said no. He doesn't even allow us into his ward now.

483
00:40:33,308 --> 00:40:36,662
He doesn't even listen to us.

484
00:40:40,171 --> 00:40:44,408
Well, you have to understand him. Right?

485
00:40:44,408 --> 00:40:49,192
If it were me, I wouldn't want to be surrounded by people taking care of me.

486
00:40:49,192 --> 00:40:51,982
It feels like I'm a waste and a burden on others.

487
00:40:51,982 --> 00:40:54,862
His self-esteem can't take it.

488
00:40:54,862 --> 00:40:59,758
Dad, how can he come to accept reality?

489
00:41:01,659 --> 00:41:05,168
Reality is easy to accept.

490
00:41:05,168 --> 00:41:09,688
But it's hard to face it.

491
00:41:10,268 --> 00:41:15,928
Que'er, if you can't even understand him, then you can't take care of him.

492
00:41:15,928 --> 00:41:19,008
Dad, I understand him, I really do.

493
00:41:19,008 --> 00:41:23,428
Every day I say to myself, "Don't be discouraged."

494
00:41:23,428 --> 00:41:26,608
"Don't be annoying. Don't be upset."

495
00:41:26,608 --> 00:41:32,588
But every day I watch him getting worse and worse, I get more upset.

496
00:41:32,588 --> 00:41:34,988
I get scared when my phone rings.

497
00:41:34,988 --> 00:41:38,695
Whenever the phone rings, I'd worry that something has happened to him.

498
00:41:38,695 --> 00:41:42,501
I-I feel so anxious. And I feel worried.

499
00:41:48,548 --> 00:41:50,248
Que'er.

500
00:41:51,408 --> 00:41:53,668
Tell me the truth.

501
00:41:54,408 --> 00:41:56,208
Do you regret it?

502
00:41:57,528 --> 00:41:59,628
No.

503
00:41:59,628 --> 00:42:01,208
All right.

504
00:42:01,848 --> 00:42:04,808
If you don't regret it, then you made the right choice.

505
00:42:04,808 --> 00:42:07,888
You have to work hard for the choice you've made.

506
00:42:09,068 --> 00:42:13,358
You don't have to go to war. But once you go, you cannot be a chicken.

507
00:42:13,908 --> 00:42:18,088
An Zhique, when I tried to stop you, you didn't listen.

508
00:42:18,088 --> 00:42:22,588
But if you want to quit or run away now, I don't allow it.

509
00:42:23,608 --> 00:42:27,512
Don't worry. We never run away.

510
00:42:27,512 --> 00:42:32,808
Okay. For your courage, I reward you to finish the soup.

511
00:42:32,808 --> 00:42:35,248
- I'll get you a bowl. 
 - Thank you.

512
00:42:36,890 --> 00:42:39,314
- Get two and we'll eat together. 
